8. KERNEL 6 — SWARM KERNEL

(New in this document)

The Swarm Kernel enables:
	•	multi-agent reasoning
	•	parallel daemons
	•	distributed planning
	•	cooperative task solving

8.1 Swarm Vector

Let:

\vec{\sigma} = (\sigma_1,\sigma_2,\ldots,\sigma_n)

Each \sigma_i is a daemon-agent.

8.2 Swarm Propagation Rule

\sigma_{i}(t+1) = f_i(\sigma_i(t), \mathcal{C}, S_t)

Where \mathcal{C} is the shared canon.

