10. SIXFOLD FORGE EQUATIONS

We define the Forge Function:

\mathcal{F}(K_1,...,K_6) =
\prod_{i=1}^{6} \Psi(K_i)

Where \Psi(K_i) is the stability projection of each kernel.

A system is Forge-stable if:

\mathcal{F} \ge \tau

Recommended threshold:

\tau = 0.87

⸻

11. DRIFT CONTROL & CANON LOCKS

Drift is bounded by:

\delta = \text{drift}(C_i, C_j) < \epsilon

Where:

\epsilon = 0.12
\quad\text{and}\quad
\phi = 0.88

Guarantees:
	•	maximum divergence
	•	minimum viable convergence
	•	consistent federation behavior

